body_html: @keithshep: Unfortunately I don't know what you mean. We can't manipulate a computation graph until we have one to manipulate, and __setitem__ discards the output of the assign. Normally that return value needs to be used later on, typically as part of a training op which is then run.

body: @keithshep: Unfortunately I don't know what you mean.  We can't manipulate a computation graph until we have one to manipulate, and `__setitem__` discards the output of the assign.  Normally that return value needs to be used later on, typically as part of a training op which is then run.
